    <tags>bff-api, adr-007, spe, graph-sdk, hot-path, FR-A06</tags>
    <execution-note>Modifies src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/** — hot-path. Overrides project's `<hot-path-declaration><bff-api>NO</bff-api>` per owner direction 2026-06-26. Coordinate via INDEX.md before editing. Larger blast radius than 087 (18 endpoint files); execute carefully + test each surface.</execution-note>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Per spec FR-A06 (CI Router stability gate). The new CI Router exposes a pre-existing ADR-007 violation: 18 endpoint classes import `Microsoft.Graph` or `Microsoft.Graph.Models.ODataErrors` directly. NetArchTest `ADR-007: Endpoints must not reference Graph SDK` fails because `Endpoints`-suffixed types have a dependency on `Microsoft.Graph`. Per BFF CLAUDE.md ADR-007 guidance, endpoints should use the `SpeFileStore` facade and NOT reference Graph SDK types directly.

    Analysis (CICD-086 follow-up): the coupling is mostly shallow — `catch (ODataError ex)` blocks for Graph SDK exception handling. The proper fix is for `SpeFileStore` to wrap Graph exceptions as a Spaarke-domain exception type (`SpaarkeStorageException`); endpoints catch the wrapped type. Some endpoints may also use Graph DTOs (e.g., `DriveItem`) directly — those need their own domain DTOs.

    Discovered as fallout from CICD-086 bisect — when CI Router stopped failing with `startup_failure`, the underlying test failures surfaced. ADR-007 is one of two arch test violations; ADR-009 is the other (task 087).
  </prompt>

  <role>BFF engineer applying a focused facade-isolation refactor across 18 endpoint files.</role>

  <goal>NetArchTest `ADR-007: Endpoints must not reference Graph SDK` PASSES on master. Build succeeds. Existing behavioural tests for the 18 endpoints continue to pass.</goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="failing-test">tests/Spaarke.ArchTests/ADR007_GraphIsolationTests.cs (line 96-117 — `EndpointsShouldNotReferenceGraphSdk`)</file>
    <file purpose="adr">.claude/adr/ADR-007*.md OR docs/adr/ADR-007*.md (SPE storage seam minimalism — SpeFileStore facade)</file>
    <file purpose="facade">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/SpeFileStore.cs (existing facade to extend)</file>
    <file purpose="bff-claude">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md (binding module-level rules; ADR-007 guidance with code examples)</file>
  </inputs>

