  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-A06">CI Router MUST achieve ≥2 consecutive successful master pushes before cutover; ADR-007 fail blocks this.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-007">Microsoft.Graph types stay isolated to Infrastructure.Graph + SpeFileStore namespaces. Endpoints + Controllers MUST NOT reference Microsoft.Graph.</constraint>
    <constraint source="root CLAUDE.md §10">BFF Hygiene: load .claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md first; publish-size delta tracked.</constraint>
    <constraint source="hot-path">Coordinate via projects/INDEX.md before editing.</constraint>
    <constraint source="testing">Update tests where Graph SDK exception types are explicitly mocked / asserted; substitute Spaarke exception type.</constraint>
    <constraint source="practical">Per-file scope: focus ONLY on removing Graph SDK references. Do NOT refactor unrelated code. Do NOT change endpoint signatures/contracts.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <design>
    **Step 0 — Inventory Graph SDK usage per file**: classify each of 18 files as:
    - **Exception-only** (most common): `using Microsoft.Graph.Models.ODataErrors;` + `catch (ODataError ex)` blocks. Fix: SpeFileStore wraps; endpoint catches wrapped type.
    - **DTO-only**: uses `DriveItem`, `Container`, etc. Fix: SpeFileStore returns domain DTOs.
    - **Mixed**: both. Apply both patterns.
    - **Deep coupling** (hopefully rare): endpoint reaches into Graph SDK behavior directly. Fix: extract to SpeFileStore method.

    **Add to SpeFileStore.cs**:
    ```csharp
    public sealed class SpaarkeStorageException : Exception
    {
        public int? StatusCode { get; }
        public string? ErrorCode { get; }
        public SpaarkeStorageException(string message, int? statusCode = null, string? errorCode = null, Exception? inner = null)
            : base(message, inner) { StatusCode = statusCode; ErrorCode = errorCode; }
    }
    ```

    **Wrap Graph exceptions** at SpeFileStore method boundaries:
    ```csharp
    try { /* existing Graph call */ }
    catch (ODataError ex)
    {
        throw new SpaarkeStorageException(
            ex.Error?.Message ?? "Storage error",
            statusCode: ex.ResponseStatusCode,
            errorCode: ex.Error?.Code,
            inner: ex);
    }
    ```

    **Endpoint refactor pattern** (per file):
    ```csharp
    // BEFORE
    using Microsoft.Graph.Models.ODataErrors;
    ...
    catch (ODataError odataError) { return Results.Problem(odataError.Error?.Message, statusCode: 500); }

    // AFTER
    using Sprk.Bff.Api.Services;  // for SpaarkeStorageException
    ...
    catch (SpaarkeStorageException ex) { return Results.Problem(ex.Message, statusCode: ex.StatusCode ?? 500); }
    ```

    Each file edit: (a) remove `using Microsoft.Graph*` imports, (b) replace catch blocks, (c) replace any direct Graph SDK type references with domain equivalents.
  </design>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read ADR-007 + BFF CLAUDE.md ADR-007 guidance + SpeFileStore.cs to understand current facade shape.</step>
    <step order="2">Add `SpaarkeStorageException` type to SpeFileStore.cs (or new sibling file Infrastructure/SpaarkeStorageException.cs).</step>
    <step order="3">Inventory each of 18 files: grep `using Microsoft.Graph` + `ODataError|ServiceException|DriveItem|Container` usage. Bucket as exception-only / DTO-only / mixed / deep.</step>
    <step order="4">Identify SpeFileStore methods that touch Graph SDK at the boundary; add wrap-and-throw blocks.</step>
    <step order="5">For each of 18 endpoint files (start with the simplest exception-only files first): remove Graph imports + replace catch blocks per pattern above.</step>
    <step order="6">For DTO usages: identify if a domain DTO already exists; if not, add one to Models/; convert SpeFileStore return values + endpoint usage.</step>
    <step order="7">After each file: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` to catch breakage early.</step>
    <step order="8">Update tests in tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ where Graph SDK exceptions are mocked → substitute SpaarkeStorageException.</step>
    <step order="9">Run ADR-007 arch tests: `dotnet test tests/Spaarke.ArchTests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~ADR007"`. All 3 facts MUST pass.</step>
    <step order="10">Run affected unit tests: `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~UploadEndpoints|ContainerEndpoints|DocumentsEndpoints"` (sampler — full set in Tier 1 CI).</step>
    <step order="11">Verify publish-size impact: `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`. Expected: negligible.</step>
    <step order="12">Step 9.5: code-review + adr-check on all 18+ modified files (FULL rigor binding).</step>
    <step order="13">Commit + push. Pair with 087 in the same PR if it lands together, OR separate PR if 087 already shipped.</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <output type="new-type">Sprk.Bff.Api.Services.SpaarkeStorageException (in SpeFileStore.cs OR sibling file)</output>
    <output type="modified">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/SpeFileStore.cs (Graph exception wrapping at boundary)</output>
    <output type="modified">18 endpoint files (Graph imports removed; catch blocks updated)</output>
    <output type="modified">Possible new files in Models/ for domain DTOs replacing Graph SDK types (if needed)</output>
    <output type="modified">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ (mock substitutions)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">SpaarkeStorageException type exists and is thrown from SpeFileStore on Graph error</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All 18 endpoint files no longer have `using Microsoft.Graph*` imports</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All 18 endpoint files no longer reference `Microsoft.Graph.*` types in any position</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` succeeds with zero new warnings</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">NetArchTest `EndpointsShouldNotReferenceGraphSdk` PASSES locally</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">NetArchTest `ControllersShouldNotReferenceGraphSdk` + `GraphTypesMustBeIsolatedToInfrastructure` STILL PASS (don't regress)</criterion>
